HEADWORD: Raptorial
<hw>Rap*to"ri*al</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧p*t⟦omac⟧"r⟦icr⟧*⟦ait⟧l)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Rapacious; living
upon prey; -- said especially of certain birds.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>Adapted for seizing prey; -- said of the legs, claws, etc., of
insects, birds, and other animals.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>Of or
pertaining to the <ord>Raptores</ord>. See <xex>Illust.</xex>
<sd>(f)</sd> of <er>Aves</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Raptorious</ent>⟦br⟧
